cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with modeling and analyzing WLANs. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses channel assignment algorithms. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is relevant as the proposed channel assignment algorithm is decentralized and does not require message passing. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a scalable cell level model for WLANs with saturated queues. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper focuses on maximizing network throughput.
